1. Introduction

This README file lists:

* The more "dynamic" information related to installation and setup of the
  WITSML Certification Testing Tool (Testing Tool). 

* Release notes associated with the Testing Tool. 

For detailed instructions on how to download, install, configure and use the Testing Tool, see
the "WITSML Certification Testing Tool: Installation and User Guide", which can be downloaded
from http://www.energistics.org/<ADD LINK WHEN WE GET IT>.


2. Testing Tool Information 

2.1 Python Utilities

To install and run the Testing Tool, you must install and configure Python, which includes
some key Python utilities.The specific utilities required may change with different versions
of the Testing Tool. 
 
Here is the most current list (as of 8 May 2013) of required Python utilities: 

*  lxml version 2.3
*  suds version 0.4
*  python-dateutil version 2.1
*  pytz version 2012d

For instructions on how to insall these utilities, see the Installation and User Guide (link above). 

3. Release Notes
	
Release Version 0.8.1 Release Date: 24 April, 2013
1. This is the release that was verified at the WITSML SIG Meeting (April 2013, Oslo) by the Certification Team to validate the installation process.